  <front>
   <head>AN EXTEMPORARY ACROSTIC.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="ten-line">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">MY Muse, once more, thy aid I humbly claim;</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Refuse not now to grace my rustic lays.</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Johnston or Pope might well befit the theme</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Or Grecian bards, who ever merit praise.</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">How dares my humble hand assume so high?</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">No common character inspires my song,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">His growing fame long since has reach'd the sky:</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">All I can say but does his virtues wrong;</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Let then my blund'ring pen in silence rest;</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Lo, silent admiration paints them best.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
